Frank   Slootman  Advisor, MapR Technologies, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 13 different industries.See Board Relationships58--
Background

		Mr. Frank Slootman serves as an Advisor of MapR Technologies, Inc. and SolidFire, Inc. Mr. Slootman has been the Chairman of the Board at ServiceNow, Inc. (formerly, Service-now.com/Glidesoft Inc) since October 25, 2016 and served as its Chief Executive Officer since May 02, 2011 until April 3, 2017 and served as its President since May 2011 until April 3, 2017. He has 25 years of experience as an entrepreneur and executive in the enterprise software industry. Mr. Slootman ... served as an Advisor of Virsto Software Corporation. Prior to ServiceNow, he served as a Venture Partner of Greylock Partners from January 11, 2011 to April 2011. His main area of focus was enterprise technology, which included virtualization, networking, storage, cloud computing and enterprise applications. Mr. Slootman served as an Advisor of EMC Corporation from January 2011 to February 2012. He served as the President of Backup Recovery Systems at EMC Corporation from July 2009 to January 2011. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Data Domain, Inc., from July 2003 to July 2009, where he blazed new trails creating a high-growth enterprise storage company. Prior to joining Data Domain, Mr. Slootman served as an Executive at Borland Software Corporation from June 2000 to June 2003. He served as a Senior Vice President of Products Operations at Borland software Corporation from 1993 to 2000 and its Vice President of Products since July 2000. Mr. Slootman served as Products Executive at Borland Software Corporation, where he ran its engineering and product management function. Prior to Borland, he held management positions for two enterprise software divisions of Compuware Corporation from March 1993 to June 2000. Mr. Slootman served as a Products Executive of Compuware Corporation. Mr. Slootman served as a General Manager of UNIFACE in Amsterdam and General Manager of the EcoSystems division in Campbell. He served several positions in Sales Support, Product Management and Marketing at Comshare Inc., and Unisys Corporation, including as Executive. Mr. Slootman started his career at Burroughs Corporation. He has been a Director of Medallia, Inc. since February 2014. He has been a Director of Pure Storage, Inc. since May 2014. Mr. Slootman has been a Director of ServiceNow, Inc. since May 2011. He has been Member of Advisory Board of Nutanix, Inc. since November 19, 2013. He serves as a Member of Executive Advisory Board at BlueData Software, Inc. Mr. Slootman serves as a Member of Advisory Board at TIBCO LogLogic Inc. He served as a Director of Imperva Inc. since August 9, 2011. Mr. Slootman served as a Director of Data Domain, Inc., from July 2003 to July 2009. He holds undergraduate and graduate degrees in Economics from the Netherlands School of Economics, Erasmus University Rotterdam.Read Full Background




